feat(news): add Nagoya visit tile (Dolladille + French Embassy)

A new news item covering Dr Charles Dolladille's visit to Nagoya
University on 13 and 14 April 2026 to meet the CANAL-AI team on site,
and the day-2 joining of Adeline Lassaux and Sonia Ciechelski from
the French Embassy in Japan to discuss the project and the
cooperation opportunities that follow from it.

Assets
- photos/Visit_Charles_Nagoya.jpg resized and re-encoded into
  site/assets/photos/visit-nagoya.webp (59 KB) and
  site/assets/photos/visit-nagoya.jpg (80 KB) as the JPEG fallback,
  both at 800x600, via Pillow. Displayed with a picture element so
  modern browsers fetch the webp.

Layout
- New .timeline__item--visual variant: spans two grid columns on
  desktop, collapses to one column below 800px. The photo sits flush
  with the card top edge inside a 4:3 figure, the date chip, title,
  and body follow beneath with standard padding. Keeps the colour
  accent stripe on top.

i18n
- Four new keys in en / ja / fr: news.visit_date, news.visit_title,
  news.visit_body, news.visit_alt (localised image alt text).
- 235 -> 239 keys; parity preserved.

Placed at the top of the news timeline as the most recent event.
